[2] Camera follows as they hit bowl's curved edge simultaneously, both lean hard into the turn with knees deeply bent, their clothes flap in the breeze with the momentum, skateboards tilt at 45-degree angle carving across the concrete, golden sunlight catches their concentrated expressions as they complete the synchronized carve.

nodes.title: Vace Reference Image Note
widgets_values: **Recommend using up to two reference image(s) for Vace in order for the High Noise stage to better latch onto your subject(s). For multiple subjects, either choose the most complex subject or create a white bg image with multiple subjects. Place them approximately where they will appear in the video.**

nodes.title: Phantom Images Note
widgets_values: **For Phantom reference images: No need for background removal if the background is simple. Maximum of 4 images. Can use multiple images for one character, but prompt carefully to avoid duplicating character.**

nodes.title: Prompting Note
widgets_values: **Include good descriptions of your characters in your prompt so that the HN stage can create a good enough approximation for the LN stage to finish up accurately.**

nodes.title: Unsampling Note
widgets_values: **Increasing number of steps_to_run in the unsampling step below will allow for more character resemblance but will lose some HN stage motion.**

nodes.title: Sampler Note
widgets_values:
### Use res_2s for quality.
### Use res_2m for speed.

nodes.title: HN Preview Note
widgets_values: **You can check the HN Preview before going through the LN sampling to see if you need to modify the prompt in order to achieve better character silhouettes and to refine your animation and actions.**

nodes.title: Models Note
widgets_values:
# Phantom A14B Test Workflow Notes v1.1

## Required Node Packs
- [RES4LYF](https://github.com/ClownsharkBatwing/RES4LYF)  
- [ComfyUI-WanVaceAdvanced](https://github.com/drozbay/ComfyUI-WanVaceAdvanced)  
- [ComfyUI-KJNodes](https://github.com/kijai/ComfyUI-KJNodes)  
- [ComfyUI-VideoHelperSuite](https://github.com/Kosinkadink/ComfyUI-VideoHelperSuite)
- [ComfyUI_essentials](https://github.com/cubiq/ComfyUI_essentials)

## Models:

- **Vace Module**: [Wan2_1-VACE_module_14B_fp8_e4m3fn.safetensors](https://huggingface.co/Kijai/WanVideo_comfy/blob/main/Wan2_1-VACE_module_14B_fp8_e4m3fn.safetensors)  
- **2.2 A14B Low Noise LoRA**: [Wan22_A14B_T2V_lora_extract_r64.safetensors](https://huggingface.co/drozbay/Wan2.2_A14B_lora_extract/blob/main/Wan22_A14B_T2V_lora_extract_r64.safetensors)

Although Vace is **only** used for the High Noise reference image in this workflow, it can be used with Phantom as well. You can use it with the Vace module or get a merged model here:
- **Vace+Phantom Merge:** [Wan2.1_VACE_Phantom](https://huggingface.co/Inner-Reflections/Wan2.1_VACE_Phantom/tree/main)
 
*(If using the LowSteps version, don't use the CausVid LoRA.)*

## Other Models Used
- [Wan2_2-T2V-A14B_HIGH_fp8_e4m3fn_scaled_KJ.safetensors](https://huggingface.co/Kijai/WanVideo_comfy_fp8_scaled/blob/main/T2V/Wan2_2-T2V-A14B_HIGH_fp8_e4m3fn_scaled_KJ.safetensors)  
- [Phantom-Wan-14B_fp8_e4m3fn.safetensors](https://huggingface.co/Kijai/WanVideo_comfy/blob/main/Phantom-Wan-14B_fp8_e4m3fn.safetensors)  
- [Wan21_CausVid_14B_T2V_lora_rank32_v2.safetensors](https://huggingface.co/Kijai/WanVideo_comfy/blob/main/Wan21_CausVid_14B_T2V_lora_rank32_v2.safetensors)
